        <headline>Heat Advisory issued August 24 at 3:30AM AKDT until August 25 at 7:00PM AKDT by NWS Juneau AK</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Temperatures up to 85 degrees expected.

* WHERE...City of Hyder.

* WHEN...Until 7 PM AKDT Monday.

* IMPACTS...Individuals not accustomed to these unusually hot
temperatures for this region may experience heat related
illnesses.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Temperatures will warm to around 80 degrees
Sunday afternoon.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids and check up on elderly and vulnerable
relatives and neighbors.

Take extra precautions when working in the sun. Wear sunscreen
and lightweight, loose fitting clothing. Try to limit strenuous
activities to early morning or evening. Take action when you see
symptoms of heat exhaustion and heat stroke

Close curtains during the daytime to reduce sun insulation into
the home and open windows at night to allow the home to cool off.
Utilize fans or community buildings with air conditioning.</instruction>
